A possible fix is to add the following in Line 385 (NumberInput.svelte) 
```ts
if (Math.abs(e.movementX) > 200) {
    // Ignores large jumps in the movementX value caused by a bug in how Inputs are reported.
	return;
}
```

200 is a magic number based on some debugging that reported numbers in the high hundreds. This also still allowed for smooth-feeling input at higher DPIs.

